# Executiva Cloud — address and complement

## Field `complement`

Present on **legal_organizations** and **organizations**. Optional; must be clearable on update.

## Screens (all must read/write complement)

- [`RegisterOrganizationView.tsx`](frontend/components/RegisterOrganizationView.tsx) — `legalComplement`
- [`LegalOrganizationsView.tsx`](frontend/components/LegalOrganizationsView.tsx) — `LegalOrganizationForm`
- [`OrganizationCompanyForm.tsx`](frontend/components/OrganizationCompanyForm.tsx) — shared company form (used by Empresas and Org jurídicas modals)

**Do not** duplicate a second company form without complement and full address validation.

## Frontend payload rules

- Use [`frontend/utils/addressPayload.ts`](frontend/utils/addressPayload.ts): `normalizeComplement`, `buildOrgAddressPayload`.
- On **update**, send `complement: null` to clear — never `undefined` (axios omits key → backend `exclude_unset` skips → stale DB value).
- **CEP lookup:** use [`useCepAutoLookup`](frontend/hooks/useCepAutoLookup.ts) on every CEP field — busca ViaCEP ao completar 8 dígitos no `onChange`, not only on blur.

## Backend

- Schemas: `OptionalComplement` in [`br_validators.py`](backend/app/core/br_validators.py) accepts `null`.
- Services: `model_dump(exclude_unset=True)` must receive explicit `null` from client to clear.

## Tests required for complement changes

- `PUT /organizations/{id}` with complement → GET returns value.
- `PUT` with `"complement": null` → cleared.
- Same for `/legal-organizations/{id}`.

See [`backend/tests/test_address_complement.py`](backend/tests/test_address_complement.py).
